main event: A spherical shaped unidentified object was observed flying above and beyond commercial aircraft near Annandale, Virginia.
interesting points: The object was observed for thirty to forty-five seconds,The object appeared to be smaller than a dime,No aerodynamic features or exhaust trails were noted,The object seemed to move somewhat faster than the aircraft at a fairly high altitude,Witnessing occurred from the left front window of an automobile traveling south on Columbia Pike.
witness description: an assistant director at the Department of Labor
